Sentencas: The delamination and degradation of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) electrode/electrolyte interface is estimated by calculating the stresses generated within the different layers of the cell.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The stresses developed in a SOFC are usually assumed to be homogenous through a cross section in the mathematical models at macroscopic scales.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: However, during the operating of these composite materials the real stresses on the multiphase porous layers might be very different than those at macro-scale.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Therefore micro-level modeling is needed for an accurate estimation of the real stresses and the performance of SOFC.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This study combines the microstructural characterization of a porous solid oxide fuel cell anode/electrolyte with two dimensional mechanical and electrochemical analyses to investigate the stress and the overpotential.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The microstructure is determined by using focused ion beam (FIB) tomography and the resulting microstructures are used to generate a solid mesh of two dimensional triangular elements.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: COMSOL Multiphysics package is employed to calculate the principal stress and Maxwell Stefan Diffusion.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The stress field is calculated from room temperature to operating temperature while the overpotential is calculated at operating temperature.
Titulo: Micro level two dimensional stress and thermal analysis anode/electrolyte interface of a solid oxide fuel cell
